<h2 id="300">3. Authorising back end users to edit orders</h2>
<div class="sectionbody">
<div class="paragraph">
<p>To authorise users of the type <strong>back end</strong> to open orders, you need to save default statuses for <strong>returns</strong> and <strong>credit notes</strong> here. No status is saved here by default.<br>
In addition, back end users must be authorised to edit orders in their respective user profile in the <strong><a href="/en/business-decisions/user-accounts-access#105">Rights » User » Menu visibilities</a></strong> menu.
Back end users also need to be authorised to create orders of the type <strong>return</strong>, <strong>warranty</strong> and <strong>repair</strong>. For this, back end users have to be authorised to edit these default status of these order types saved in the <strong>System » System setting » Orders » Settings</strong> menu. The authorisations are assigned in the user profile of the back end user in the <strong><a href="/en/business-decisions/user-accounts-access#105">Rights » User » Menu visibilities</a></strong> menu.</p>
</div>
